'''Ismael Díaz de León''' (born 12 May 1997) is a Panamanian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Winger (association football)|left winger]] for [[Liga MX]] club [[Club León|León]] and the [[Panama national football team|Panama national team]].

==Club career==
Born in [[Panama City]], Díaz made his professional debut for [[Tauro F.C.|Tauro]] on 2 September 2012 against [[Alianza F.C. (Panama)|Alianza]], aged just 15 years and 2 months.<ref>[http://www.taurofc.com/comunicado_mayor_Ismael_Diaz.php Ismael Díaz nominado a los COS Awards] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304135936/http://www.taurofc.com/comunicado_mayor_Ismael_Diaz.php |date=4 March 2016 }} - Tauro F.C. {{in lang|es}}</ref> He had a trial with Dutch club [[PSV Eindhoven]] in summer 2014.<ref>[http://www.ed.nl/sport/voetbal/psv/isma%C3%ABl-diaz-17-op-stage-bij-psv-1.4476771 Ismaël Diaz (17) op stage bij PSV] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304140819/http://www.ed.nl/sport/voetbal/psv/isma%C3%ABl-diaz-17-op-stage-bij-psv-1.4476771 |date=4 March 2016 }} - Eindhovens Dagblad {{in lang|nl}}</ref> In August 2015, he joined Portuguese club [[FC Porto]] on a loan.<ref>[http://www.prensa.com/deportes/Panameno-Ismael-FC-Porto-Portugal_0_4277572358.html Ismael Díaz es el nuevo fichaje del FC Porto de Portugal] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170801161551/http://www.prensa.com/deportes/Panameno-Ismael-FC-Porto-Portugal_0_4277572358.html |date=1 August 2017 }} - La Prensa {{in lang|es}}</ref> On 2017 the loan ended due to [[FC Porto]] order.

On 31 August 2019, Díaz joined [[Académico de Viseu F.C.|Académico Viseu]].<ref>[https://www.panamaamerica.com.pa/deportes/ismael-diaz-ya-viste-el-10-con-el-academico-de-viseu-1142753 Ismael Díaz ya viste el 10 con el Académico de Viseu], panamaamerica.com.pa, 31 August 2019</ref> He left the club at the end of the year and returned to [[Tauro F.C.|Tauro]] in January 2020.<ref>[https://futbolcentroamerica.com/noticias/Ismael-Diaz-vuelve-al-Tauro-y-hace-una-gran-promesa-20200114-0004.html Ismael Díaz vuelve al Tauro y hace una gran promesa], futbolcentroamerica.com, 14 January 2020</ref>

On 6 January 2022, [[Ecuadorian Serie A]] club [[C.D. Universidad Católica del Ecuador|Universidad Católica]], announced the signing of Ismael Díaz, in time for the start of the [[2022 Ecuadorian Serie A]] season, as well as the [[2022 Copa Libertadores]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.primicias.ec/noticias/jugada/universidad-catolica-refuerza-panameno-ismael-diaz/|title = Universidad Católica se refuerza con el atacante panameño Ismael Díaz}}</ref> Díaz had made an immediate impact during his first two weeks at the club, scoring 2 league goals in his first 2 matches, which earned him being selected "Best Player of Matchday 1 of Serie A". Díaz then scored 2 more goals in the second stage of the Libertadores Cup group stage qualifiers, helping La Católica to a 3–1 aggregate win over Bolivian side [[Club Bolívar]].<ref>https://www.rpctv.com/futbol-internacional/futbol/ismael-diaz-anota-el-partido-vuelta-la-copa-libertadores-n5670296 |date=2 March 2022</ref>

On 25 July 2025, Díaz joined Mexican club [[Club León|León]].

==International career==
He played at the [[2013 FIFA U-17 World Cup]] in the [[United Arab Emirates]] and the [[2015 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] in [[New Zealand]].<ref>{{FIFA player|4006}}</ref>

Díaz made his senior debut for Panama in an August 2014 friendly match against [[Cuba national football team|Cuba]].

In June 2018 he was announced to be part of Panama's squad for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in [[Russia]], and he made one appearance as a substitute against [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] in a 3–0 loss during the group stage.<ref>{{cite web| url = https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb| title = Revealed: Every World Cup 2018 squad - Final 23-man lists {{!}} Goal.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=Belgium 3-0 Panama (Jun 18, 2018) Final Score |work=[[ESPN]] |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match?gameId=498190 |access-date=2023-07-09}}</ref>

On 8 July 2023, Díaz scored a hat-trick against [[Qatar national football team|Qatar]] during the quarter-finals of the [[2023 CONCACAF Gold Cup]] in a 4–0 win.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2023-07-08 |title=Ismael Diaz scores hat-trick to earn Panama semis berth with win over Qatar |work=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]] |url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/2023/07/09/64aa0bbe268e3eac638b459b.html |access-date=2023-07-08}}</ref> On 24 June 2025, he scored another hat-trick in the Gold Cup, this time against [[Jamaica national football team|Jamaica]].

